    "description": {
      "value": "<p>If you have any temporary hit points remaining from a casting of @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.7uLBk0MRAiNUHKR6]{Armor of Agathys (The Redeemer)}, you can use an action to project that energy in a 60-foot line, 15-feet wide, removing the remaining temporary hit points in the process. Anyone in this area must make a Dexterity save (DC = 8 + Strength modifier + your proficiency bonus) or take damage on a failed save equal to the amount of temporary hit points removed plus the damage equal to a damage roll for this weapon (with whatever bonuses apply at the time of casting), or half as much on a successful one. The damage is both radiant and fire, and whichever damage is higher against each target applies.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-SvvTk5gdagjaTQkV\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>When you use this ability, you will have to manually remove any temporary HP removed by it.</p></section>",
